Description: OLED-safe black screensaver for Ubuntu (Wayland + X11)
 A lightweight, OLED-friendly black screensaver for modern Ubuntu/GNOME
 desktops running Wayland or X11. It keeps long-running tasks (downloads,
 builds, scripts) alive while you are away, without locking the screen.
 .
 Features:
  * Pure black fullscreen window - OLED pixels are physically off,
    giving near-zero power draw and zero burn-in risk.
  * Status text drifts every few seconds to prevent static burn-in.
  * Mouse cursor hidden while active.
  * Screen lock, screensaver and dimming disabled while running.
  * System suspend inhibited via systemd-inhibit so background work
    is not killed.
  * All GNOME power/lock settings are snapshotted and restored on exit.
 .
 Once installed, run the `screensaver` command and press ESC or click
 anywhere to exit.
